When working with very large amounts of data, unfiltered SOQL or SOSL queries can quickly cause [governor limit](https://developer.salesforce.com/docs/atlas.en-us.apexcode.meta/apexcode/apex_gov_limits.htm) exceptions.
https://docs.pmd-code.org/pmd-doc-7.13.0/pmd_rules_apex_performance.html#avoidnonrestrictivequeries
```


public class Something {
    public static void main( String[] as ) {
        Account[] accs1 = [ select id from account ];  // Bad
        Account[] accs2 = [ select id from account limit 10 ];  // better

        List<List<SObject>> searchList = [FIND 'map*' IN ALL FIELDS RETURNING Account (Id, Name), Contact, Opportunity, Lead]; // bad
    }
}

